================================================================
This is a grab bag of various Perl scripts, mostly numerical,
and all rather old at this point.  Among the non-numerical
ones are some Unix-style replacement scripts, from my NT days.
John Kerl
kerl.john.r@gmail.com
2012-07-28
================================================================

Descriptions:

Makefile generator ("yet another make-make"):
* yamm [scripts/fundam/yamm],
* sample program 1 for yamm [yamm_ex1],
* sample program 2 for yamm [yamm_ex2].

Substitute for makeindex which correctly handles alphabetization of text including \mathbb etc. in LaTeX files:
* kmkidx [kmkidx].

Tools for formatting and manipulating tabular data in plain ASCII:
* colprint [colprint],
* mwxprint [mxwprint],
* parside [parside],
* interleave [interleave],
* creach [creach],
* twoper [twoper],
* xpose [xpose],
* cpick [cpick],
* dashes [dashes],
* caytex [caytex],
* mattex [mattex].

Tools for large-scale search and replace:
* krepl [krepl],
* mrepl [mrepl].
* Variants of familiar tools:
* bffind /bffind],
* mgrep [mgrep].

Windows workalikes for familiar Unix tools:
* kbc [kbc],
* grep.pl [grep.pl],
* head.pl [head.pl],
* tail.pl [tail.pl],
* uniq.pl [uniq.pl],
* wc.pl [wc.pl],
* whereis.pl [whereis.pl],
* My_win_glob.pm [My_win_glob.pm],
* w.pl [w.pl],
* notes about Perl and Windows file associations [perl-on-windows-notes.txt],
* toc.pl [toc.pl]  which works around the Windows association/redirection bug.

Unix workalikes for familiar Windows tools:
* grepr [grepr],
* lsr [lsr],
* rmr [rmr].

fixrlinks [fixrlinks.pl] :
When I rsync -rtlz between hosts on which the spelling of my home directory
differs (e.g. /u5/kerl on one and /home/kerl on the other), rsync doesn't
change the symlink referents.  This script can be run after an rsync to fix
that.

finddang [finddang.pl] : Reports on dangling symlinks.

Miscellaneous text manipulation:
* upcase [upcase],
* downcase [downcase],
* scrunch [scrunch],
* printtwice [printtwice],
* printtwicej [printtwicej],
* printthricej [printthricej],
* chop [chop],
* dspc [dspc],
* dspcw [dspcw],
* linesort [linesort],
* detab [detab],
* retab [retab],
* fdiff [fdiff],
* nocolon [nocolon],
* wordfreq [wordfreq].

Numerical calculus:
* series estimation [numseries],
* another series estimation [numseries2],
* 1-D numerical differentiation [numderiv1],
* 1-D numerical integration [numint1],
* 2-D numerical integration [numint2],
* path integral one way [numint3],
* same path integral another way [numint4].

Floating-point matrix arithmetic:
* Matrix multiply [pmatmul],
* matrix add [pmatadd],
* matrix inverse [pmatinv],
* determinant [pdet],
* row reduction [prred],
* row echelon form [prech],
* row rank [prank],
* kernel basis [pkerbas],
* Gram-Schmidt orthonormalization [pgramsch],
* Jacobi eigensolver for real symmetric matrices [prseigsys],
* elementwise vector sum [pvecadd],
* elementwise vector difference [pvecsub],
* elementwise vector product [pvecmul],
* vector times scalar [pvecsmul],
* dot product [pdot],
* vector-to-scalar sum [psve],
* vector-to-scalar sum of squares [psvesq],
* matrix library file PMATLIB.pm [PMATLIB.pm].

Generators of special-purpose matrices:
* Hilbert matrix (famously near-singular) [pmkhilbmx],
* identity [pmkI],
* DDA A [pmkddaA],
* DDA Q [pmkddaQ].

Fast Fourier transform and associated tools:
* radix-2 FFT [pfft],
* complex rectangular-to-polar [prect2polar],
* complex polar-to-rectangular [ppolar2rect],
* power sum (for discrete Parseval) [ppowersum].

Data generators for testing FFT implementations:
* pcisgen [pcisgen],
* pspikegen [pspikegen],
* phatgen [phatgen],
* prampgen [prampgen],
* prandgen [prandgen].

Misc. numerical routines:
* Lagrange interpolation [lagrinterp],
* partial sums [sumupx],
* binomial coefficients and Pascal's triangle [binc],
* extended GCD using Blankinship's algorithm [pgcd].
